The paper deals with coding theory, specifically constacyclic codes over finite chain rings. This falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the matrix-product structure of these codes, which could potentially fall under categories such as cryptography (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), signal processing (cs.SI), or machine learning (cs.LG).
